Biden
Time
-----

Last Friday, I whipped out a favorite old royal blue Herm=C3=A8s tie,
hastily constructed a four-in-hand knot, brushed the lint off a trusty Broo=
ks suit, and started off for a special evening in Washington, D.C.=E2=80=94=
the final media pals holiday party of the Biden era.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

The executive mansion is a short trot from The Riggs, my second home in the=
 capital, and the historic building emerges only gradually upon approach am=
ong the low-slung mix of neoclassical piles that defined
postcolonial Washington and the sleek, Lego-like office mini-towers that do=
minate the modern vista. The architectural dialogue between past and presen=
t is a defining leitmotif of the town, and it=E2=80=99s rarely more punctua=
ted than during the interregnum between administrations. As my wife and I q=
ueued up to enter the building along 15th Street=E2=80=94a slithering relay=
 through various Secret Service checkpoints=E2=80=94we overheard a number o=
f other well-wishers wonder aloud whether Trump would
continue the party next year. (During his first administration, he=E2=80=99=
d moved off the event after the first year.) It was a valid question, and a=
 light reflection, perhaps, of a little media myopia.=C2=A0

Meta ( https://ai.meta.com/open/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS=
+%2812%2F28%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F21%2F=
24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c6061=
7da42abd12a )

Inside, the grand ballroom and salons were exquisitely decorated
with stunning white lighting, holiday bells dangling from red ribbons, and =
miniature silhouettes of dove-like creatures floating above us. It was beau=
tiful: the Ralph Lauren-ized vision of America that we all hold somewhere i=
nside of us, amid the official portraits of the officeholders and their spo=
uses. The White House staff usually moves the artwork around, but I was abl=
e to spot the depictions of both Obamas, Lady Bird, Hillary,
Bill, Eleanor, the famous image of Lincoln, and both portrayals of Kennedy=
=E2=80=94the one painted before that day in Dallas, and the subsequent one =
with his eyes askance.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Mingling throughout were CNN anchors, NBC News stars, Washington Post colum=
nists, Atlantic cover story artists, the founders of Axios, Puck cinematic
universe fixture Sally Buzbee, my buddies from BPI, etcetera. It was a rare=
 night in Washington, refreshingly devoid of cynicism and filled with the p=
romise of citizenship. Everyone in that room, more or less, had vociferousl=
y criticized the president on their air or in their copy=E2=80=94for being =
selfish, for holding on too long, for pardoning Hunter, for effectively han=
ding the people=E2=80=99s house back to Trump=E2=80=94and yet, they all wan=
ted to gather to shake his hand a final
time and wish him well on his journey back to private life. Meanwhile, the =
senescent president could have easily declined the event this year on accou=
nt of his travels, the exigencies of winding down his administration, or so=
me other passable white lie. (Trust me, social Washington was already aflut=
ter with commentary about the fact that the Bidens were throwing fewer holi=
day parties this season=E2=80=A6) Instead, he manned the rope line, greetin=
g hundreds of well-wishers with a firm, if frail,
handshake.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

As I prepared to disembark to the real world, I exchanged holiday greetings=
 with Ben LaBolt, the affable and innovative White House communications dir=
ector, who is seemingly off to the higher calling of the private sector. He=
 had the look of a man at the end of a long journey=E2=80=94pensive, tired =
yet restless, slightly uncertain but filled with curiosity. What a nice way=
 to
greet the new year, I thought to myself.

=C2=A0

These sorts of passages are the true theme of Washington=E2=80=94and beyond=
=2E We=E2=80=99re in for a brave new world=
 starting next month, and the plotl=
ines are already being clearly delineated by my generationally talented par=
tners at Puck. In a series of characteristically brilliant pieces, Lauren S=
